Title: Dedicates a portion of the state highway system in the village of Unionville to the "Appalachian Trail"
Summary: Dedicates a portion of state highway 284 in the village of Unionville as the "Appalachian Trail Highway".
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the highway law, in relation to dedicating a portion of the state highway system in the village of Unionville as the "Appalachian Trail Highway"
